Cape Town – An off-duty police sergeant has been shot dead in Khayelitsha. The 40-year-old officer, who was stationed at the Mitchells Plain detectives unit, was visiting Site B on Sunday night, said police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana. Three unidentified men shot him and robbed him of his cellphone. He was unarmed at the time and his murder is being investigated. Meanwhile, provincial police commissioner Khombinkosi Jula has lauded those behind the discovery of a dagga laboratory and about 200g of cocaine and chemicals used to manufacture drugs in a house in a Villa Bianco Flat, Bellville. A 31-year-old man was arrested on charges of dealing in drugs following an Intelligence driven operation conducted on Saturday in conjunction with members of the Rapid Rail National Response Team. He is expected to appear in the Bellville Magistrate’s Court today. “Members received information about where suspected dealing in narcotics occurred and acted swiftly. At the premises, members found a dagga laboratory, approximately 200g of cocaine and chemicals used to manufacture drugs which they seized,” said police spokesperson FC van Wyk.